DOC.TEXT:
   Here is the the 68-32 roll call by which the
Senate voted Tuesday to restrict future growth of U.S. imports of
textiles and apparel products to 1 percent a year and freeze
imports of non-rubber footwear at 1989 levels.
   On this vote, a ``yes'' vote was a vote to restrict further
imports and a ``no'' vote was a vote to allow their growth to
continue.
   Voting ``yes'' were 46 Democrats and 22 Republicans.
   Voting ``no'' were 9 Democrats and 23 Republicans.
   Adams, D-Wash., no; Akaka, D-Hawaii, yes; Armstrong, R-Colo.,
no; Baucus, D-Mont., no; Bentsen, D-Texas, yes.
